elements.title: Isatou Nyang
elements.contents: ... that after the Paralympics, Gambian athlete Isatou Nyang (pictured) continued to train at night, and during the day she would beg to support herself?

elements.title: Nun saget Dank und lobt den Herren
elements.contents: ... that "Nun saget Dank und lobt den Herren", a 16th-century German hymn based on Psalm 118, was rewritten and shortened in the 20th century for a hymnal of the Swiss Reformed Church?

elements.title: Devon Powers
elements.contents: ... that Devon Powers argues in Writing the Record that 1960s counter-culture music journalists Richard Goldstein and Robert Christgau acted as public intellectuals despite working outside of academia?

elements.title: Headreach Island
elements.contents: ... that Headreach Island had 175 acres (71 ha) of farmland in 1923, but by 1974 was mostly marshland or underwater?

elements.title: Telok Ayer MRT station
